<h1> Times Square </h1>

<p> Times Square is a major commercial intersection, tourist destination, entertainment hub, and neighborhood in Midtown Manhattan, New York City. It is formed by the junction of Broadway, Seventh Avenue, and <br> 
42nd Street. Together with adjacent Duffy Square, Times Square is a bowtie-shaped space five blocks long between 42nd and 47th Streets.[2]</p>

<p>Brightly lit at all hours by numerous digital billboards and advertisements as well as businesses offering 24/7 service, <br>
Times Square is sometimes referred to as "the Crossroads of the World,”[3]” the Center of the Universe,”[4] <br>
"the heart of the Great White Way",[5][6][7] “the Center of the Entertainment Universe”,[8] and "the heart of the world".</p>
